HEADWORD: Glycyrrhiza
<hw>Glyc`yr*rhi"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <?/; <?/ sweet + <?/ root. Cf. <er>Licorice</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of papilionaceous
herbaceous plants, one species of which (<spn>G. glabra</spn>), is the
licorice plant, the roots of which have a bittersweet mucilaginous
taste.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The root of <spn>Glycyrrhiza
glabra</spn> (liquorice root), used as a demulcent, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glycyrrhizimic</ent>⟦br⟧
